Bug 518629 - Update message header delete icon to 'restore' for IMAP-deleted messages. r=vineet

When using the "mark it as deleted" IMAP model, the message header delete
button's action correctly toggles to "undelete", but its icon incorrectly
remained a trash can. The underlying JavaScript already correctly sets
`data-imap-deleted="true"` on the button in this state.

This patch fixes the visual mismatch by updating the CSS to display
`var(--icon-restore)` when the `data-imap-deleted` attribute is true.
This change also ensures the header button's appearance is visually consistent
with the 'Delete' column in the message list pane, which already uses the
restore icon for this state.

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295504

diff --git a/mail/themes/shared/mail/messageHeader.css b/mail/themes/shared/mail/messageHeader.css
--- a/mail/themes/shared/mail/messageHeader.css
+++ b/mail/themes/shared/mail/messageHeader.css
@@ -267,8 +267,12 @@ mail-tagfield[collapsed="true"] {
 .hdrTrashButton {
   list-style-image: var(--icon-trash);
 }
 
+.hdrTrashButton[data-imap-deleted="true"] {
+  list-style-image: var(--icon-restore);
+}
+
 #attachmentSaveAllSingle,
 #attachmentSaveAllMultiple {
   list-style-image: var(--icon-download);
 }
